author: NICOLE HENSLEY
title: Woman busted in assassination of Kim Jong-un's half brother
text:
Kim Jong Nam, left, was killed at a Malaysian airport. His half-brother is North Korean leader Kim Jong-un, right. (Shizuo Kambayashi, Wong Maye-E/AP) NEW YORK DAILY NEWS Wednesday, February 15, 2017, 5:05 AM 
Malaysian police captured a woman in the assassination probe of North Korean leader Kim Jong-un's older half brother. 
Cops arrested a 28-year-old suspect toting a Vietnamese passport at the Kuala Lumpur International Airport on Wednesday morning where Kim Jong Nam was reportedly slain with a poisoned pen. 
The woman was identified by the Royal Malaysia Police as Doan Thi Huong, of Nam Dinh. 
She was pictured in surveillance footage linked to Kim's death, police said. The dictator's estranged sibling was reportedly pen emitting a toxic spray in the airport's shopping concourse on Monday. Police officers wait at the forensic department entrance at a hospital in Putrajaya. (Daniel Chan/AP) 
Kim died while being rushed to a nearby hospital. 
The exiled son of Kim Jong-il fled North Korea in 2001.
